76561198108269527,Recommended,321980,12604911,"Posted: 23 October, 2014",all,quantum_jak,"Time to update this review. A substantial amount of work has been done since its early access release. Now this game is quite fun to play for extended periods of time. There is a lot to explore, quests available from townsfolk, random dungeons, monsters roaming the land. It is a very fun free-roaming sandbox arpg. Grand Theft Fable?The gameplay is pretty basic 3rd person arpg. Not isometric like Diablo et al, but presented in an over- the-shoulder 3rd person perspective like Fable(or GTA). You can be nice and help people, or you can steal from everybody and be a murderous thug. I am sure that at some point a story will be added, but right now it is more of a free-roaming sandbox.The combat is slightly loose, and could be tightened up a little bit. For the most part combat works as expected. Sometimes it is a little hard to time strikes perfectly. This is not bad enough to be a serious problem,  just a minor quibble with the gameplay which I'm sure can be adjusted. Even if they leave the combat as is, I'd still be happy with the game. But I could be  happier.I especially appreciate the graphics, which are slightly cute and cartoonish, yet stunning at the same time with the settings maxed out at 1080p.The developers are definitely working dilligently to complete the game.""Our goal is to make Hardland one of the great action adventure RPGs.""""We want to make Hardland a world full of interesting characters, creatures, quests, and mysterious places. We will not dictate how you should play this game. We merely set the stage and let you make your own decisions. ""I think the developers are well on their way to realizing those goals.Old review:This game is far from done. The art and graphics are great (see screenshots etc...), the gameplay is coming together(per developer 70% complete).  The game world, on the other hand, still has a way to go (per developer only 20% complete). When complete, I think it will be a great open world fantasy arpg.I would not buy this if you are looking for something you can put lots of hours into immediately. However if you want to support what I think will become a very fun game.... I can't wait to play this game when the gameworld is closer to 75% ready!"
