,Recommended,321980,13155566,"Posted: 29 November, 2014",all,MajorReisman17,"Just wanted to give my first impressions. Where to start :-).Firstly game enviroments feels very much like Cube world more than minecraft in my opinion. The terrain is still somewhat disjointed in places  e.g uneven terrain especially roads (unlike Cubeworlds beautiful smoothness in creating terrain and especially roads through the terrain). The terrain has some great effects when travelling from biome to biome (much better than Cube world in my opinion). Overall still really enjoying the terrain and just wandering about (which I did a lot in Cube world). Towns seem to be in the game but other than the  starting town (with walls around it) the other towns just seem barren by comparrison (just a few  buildings scattered quite far from one another  and  no road going  through them in most cases.  I hope the developers plan to tweak and add  more to the current towns on roads and make them unique in each biome (eg different looking buildings - e.g. in forrest roofs made out of leaves, plains roofs made out of hay etc......). Gameplay is interesting. It is somewhat basic at this time (although being an Alpha I expect that will hopefully change for the better). Finding items out in the wild is very limited at this time (the best thing I found randomly was a Magnificent Key). Most of the time you will find chests with no keys or barrels filled with fruit (very useful). Keys in particular seem very hard to find (too hard in my opinion). You can level up as you explore/fight although the effects do not seem to do much at this time (im my opinion). And yes I know it does raise my health  as I level up. Also have not found any major weapon upgrades other that armor shoulder pads at this time. one time found a spellbook (from a dead friendly AI) and could not figure how to use it, and  also a glowing green staff.  (most of my time was exploring anyway so not important). I feel this game has alot of potential like Cube world. I hope they are able to continue to work on this jem. The graphics look great although this game seems to struggle on my system (i5- 3550,  8gb ram and a 295 GTX graphics card). Make sure you turn down AA expecially. I was having a slide show when trying to run on Ultra with 4x AA enabled. Much better with Medium with 2x AA enabled although I does still seem to chug at times (obviously being an Alpha I also understand that tuning with come later - maybe at the  beta stage). Basically at the end of  the  day I do not regret purchasing this game at all and really looking forward to what they do next. I have already read on the work on the terrain generation (great) and I hope they can flesh the game out (more weapons,armors etc..) and would like to see some variations on  monsters for specific biomes (e.g. monsters in the snow biome will not be seen in the jungle biome for instance). Great job to the developers. I do not regreat investing my $14.95 purchase price towards supporting this game into a bright future. Thank you four your hard work."
76561198026912947,Not Recommended,321980,24861787,"Posted: 12 August, 2016",all,louis.john.is.not,"This title is still waaaaay back from being close to completion. It only looks good graphically (if your machine can sustain it!), but as far as gameplay and mechanics go, it still feels very much like a skeleton of what it should be. There is no intro or apparent purpose which is given to you as soon as the game starts; enemy difficulty half a minute into the game is quite steep; dialogues are as generic as they come and seem to make zero sense; NPC personalities are far from being fleshed out; puzzles? strategy? quests? How do you play this game? what are you supposed to do? This game has been so long on Early Access but yet I have no idea what this game is supposed to be.If the core of the gameplay is in action, the game is very unbalanced and not user friendly early on; the game does stuff like throwing a band of mini goblins, a boar (tough to kill at starting level) and a fire hurling knight which will totally demolished you in 4 hits. Your character will explode in loot you didn't even knew you had, because (you guessed it) you just started playing a few seconds ago...My suggestion to the devs: it's best to set down the gameplay and fix the little content to a good point, than making something too ambitious and ending with a lot of loose ends. The game may promise well, but it needs a direction and a sense of progression, most of all, to be enjoyable rather than frustrating."
,Recommended,321980,13771032,"Posted: 1 January, 2015",all,ottermeat,"game isnt finished yet, but i like where its going enough to recommend.TL;DR i love this game, but if you dont like cutesy graphics, you might not.Hardland got it all right for me, and i definately reccomend it. The graphics are fun and different, very good IMO.  A lot of the equipment is bigger than your character and won't magically resize to fit you like in most games, so some things are humourously large. There is a fun faction system to play with. The combat is a bit simplistic at the time of writing this, but that goes well with the game's style honestly. I also like the way they handle the armor system, and how it can be destroyed to get at the soft bits (unless you're fighting a skeleton) underneath. I think all this stuff is very cool, but if you are the kind of person that needs flawless, in depth combat and want all your games to look like far cry or COD, this might not be what you are looking for. For everyone else: buy this game now seriously."
