76561198110587703,Not Recommended,321980,17990450,"Posted: 11 September, 2015",all,A Nym,"Having bought into this game in the very early access, I was pleasantly surprised by the large, seemingly procedural world and emergent storyline that brought with it. While the art direction wasn't and still isn't my cup of tea, it seemed to have great potential if expanded on and better optimized. With this in mind, I decided to wait a few months and see what the devs would come up with given time.Imagine my surprise then when I downloaded it again mid-year, only to find it had not only failed to improve in practically every aspect, but even regressed. Gone was the vast open world I'd enjoyed, replaced short chain of miniscule pregenerated maps and an endless, empty dungeon. Removed was the feeling of exploration and progression, the excitement and fun replaced with a struggle to progress anywhere that felt far more like a chore. The devs have promised to expand upon the existing game in the past few months, but so far the best they've managed is to shoehorn in a handful of mechanics that were in the original draft.Elephant people and elven wizards aside, their focus on prettier graphics and visual effects over replay value and depth will ultimately lead to just another average mid-tier indie RPG. Assuming they stay the course with their new design plan, I can't recommend this game over the plethora of other such games available on steam."
