76561198061128041,Recommended,321980,15684748,"Posted: 4 May, 2015",all,KrimsonVagus,"Cute graphics + destructible enviroments + Hack and Slash 3rd person RPG similar to Dark Souls (but more casual)Are you getting exhausted from playing games with a dark intimidating atmosphere that take themselves too seriously? Do you want to play a game that is easy to access and makes you smile and laugh without being too silly? Then Hardland is the game for you.Hardland has a perfect balance between moderately challenging gameplay and the fun of exploration and looting. This game was not designed to challenge your skills, but rather it was designed to make you smile. And guess what... we all need to take a break sometimes and enjoy something goofy, right?In the Early Access version, you start with a default warrior character who gains experience by killing creatures (and completing some quests). There is no skill tree at this point. Gaining levels will simply improve your health and damage and allow you to equip higher level items. Simple and straightforward.Most environmental object can be destroyed (except very large objects like trees and buildings) and almost always contains something you can use including gold, simple weapons and healing items.So you can see the game has some sandbox and open-world features. The only thing that would complete the picture would be a skill tree and crafting system, preferably the latter. I'm not sure if these are being planned or not, but they would definitely make the game a more decent experience.But the most amusing features in this game would be:the wacky enemies and the items that you can loot from their corpses.You can kill merchants (or zombie merchants) to take their guns. You can kill a skeleton wearing a chicken mask to take his mask that allows you to attract chicken. You can kill a goblin to take his enchanted hammer or axe. Everything you see can be yours if you can take it by force! This makes you want to explore and find MORE enemies to destroy and loot. That would be the most fun feature of the game right now.The combat itself is nothing too special. You can exploit the enemy's blind spots and just mash the attack button until they're dead. Not too challenging, they will always hit you the exact same way, very predictable. And their hit detection is not great. Perhaps this will be improved in the future?So as you can see, there is lots of potential and lots of room for improvement. They need to add more NPCs, the quests have to be elaborated more, the quest bugs must be fixed. The map needs to be made more clear (I can't find the entrance to a dungeon using the map). The enemies must be made more challenging.One annoying thing right now is that every time I try to help the town guard fight an enemy, if I attack the guard ONLY ONCE BY MISTAKE >> he will chase me and try to kill me non-stop!Of course, there is no crime system right now, so you can pretty much kill all guards outside the town and no one would care.If you like the concept based on this description, feel free to support the developers and buy it now. This is a good game to buy for your kids if you are introducing them to the 3rd person RPG genre (particularly if they are less than 12 years old), but it's also ok for your own casual game requirements. Otherwise, just keep your expectations to a healthy minimum until the full release.Early Access rating : 7/10You can check out my playthrough below for more details. I hope you like it! :)https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bePp-_l56QI&list=PLP90c0klxXzipUdOdeekhdEXKQU3zUFwP"
